%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20the%20DIPS%20parents%3A%20Double%20Income%2C%20Public%20School.%20They've%20got%20it%20better%20than%20the%20POLKs%2C%20or%20Parents%20of%20Little%20Kids.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22black%20and%20white%20photo%20of%20children%20at%20school%20desks%20in%20the%201940s%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d900e56080194819f9df4f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22751%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChildren%20attending%20free%20public%20school%2C%20much%20to%20the%20delight%20of%20their%20parents'%20wallets.%3Cp%3EArchive%20Photos%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EParents%20are%20divided%20economically%20among%20one%20key%20line%3A%20if%20their%20kids%20are%20old%20enough%20for%20public%20school.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcost-of-childcare-crisis-get-worse-in-september-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChildcare%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20an%20obstacle%20to%20families'%20financial%20goals%2C%20like%20home%20ownership.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20DIPS%20(Double%20Income%2C%20Public%20School)%20parents%20are%20out%20of%20the%20woods%20on%20those%20crushing%20day%20care%20payments.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20my%20colleague%20Alcynna%20Lloyd%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdinks-buy-homes-parents-spend-most-income-on-mortgage-childcare-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESorry%2C%20parents%3A%20The%20American%20Dream%20is%20only%20for%20DINKS%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Which%2C%20well%2C%20depressing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELloyd%20describes%20how%20the%20cost%20of%20childcare%20means%20buying%20a%20home%20is%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20lots%20of%20families%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20considering%20today's%20high%20interest%20rates%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-bubble-home-prices-stay-high-crash-real-estate-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20home%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20means%20the%20homeownership%20dream%20is%20something%20only%20DINKS%20(Double%20Income%2C%20No%20Kids)%20can%20afford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EZillow%20found%20that%20in%2031%20of%20the%20largest%2050%20US%20metropolitan%20areas%20with%20available%20childcare-cost%20data%2C%20families%20looking%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20could%20expect%20to%20spend%20more%20than%2060%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20mortgage%20and%20childcare%20costs.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESome%20areas%20were%20even%20costlier%3A%20It%20found%20that%3Cstrong%3E%20parents%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20San%20Diego%20would%20need%20to%20dedicate%20as%20much%20as%20121%25%20and%20113%25%20of%20their%20income.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20(In%20those%20areas%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20buying%20a%20typical%20home%20and%20childcare%20is%20so%20big%20relative%20to%20the%20median%20income%20that%20Zillow's%20calculation%20resulted%20in%20figures%20over%20100%25.)%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EPut%20another%20way%3A%20In%20areas%20with%20high%20real%20estate%20prices%2C%20like%20California%2C%20a%20mortgage%20plus%20day%20care%20is%20more%20than%20the%20median%20family%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYikes.%20Grim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20like%20to%20suggest%20one%20glass-half-full%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20this%2C%20however.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhome-prices-drop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehousing%20crisis%20is%20real%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20yes%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-are-quitting-struggling-at-work-because-of-childcare-crisis-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildcare%20system%20is%20fundamentally%20broken%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%2C%20both%20for%20its%20high%20costs%20and%20its%20low%20pay%20for%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20double%20whammy%20of%20housing%20plus%20childcare%20costs%20doesn't%20hit%20all%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20just%20parents%20of%20very%20young%20kids.%20Something%20magical%20typically%20happens%20when%20kids%20turn%205%3A%20They%20go%20to%20free%20public%20kindergarten%2C%20and%20those%20debilitating%20childcare%20costs%20start%20to%20melt%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(A%20few%20obvious%20caveats%3A%20Not%20%3Cem%3Eall%3C%2Fem%3E%20kids%20go%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnces.ed.gov%2Ffastfacts%2Fdisplay.asp%3Fid%3D372%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic%20school%2C%20but%20most%20do%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20children%20require%20special%20services%20or%20therapies%20that%20may%20continue%20to%20be%20costly.%20School%20usually%20ends%20around%203%20p.m.%2C%20and%20there%20are%20costs%20for%20after-school%20care.%20However%2C%20after-school%20programs%20or%20an%20afternoon%20babysitter%20are%20typically%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-expensive-cities-for-childcare-daycare-us-affordable-care-cost-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20full-time%20day%20care%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDividing%20parents%20into%20DINKs%20vs.%20POLKS%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20it's%20not%20just%20%26quot%3BParents%26quot%3B%20vs%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-dinks-winning-childfree-economy-finances-income-vacation-retirement-kids-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDINKs%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20in%20how%20we're%20thinking%20about%20who%20can%20afford%20home%20ownership.%20%26quot%3BParents%26quot%3B%20can%20be%20divided%20into%20two%20separate%20groups%3A%20those%20who%20are%20still%20paying%20for%20day%20care%20vs.%20those%20with%20kids%20old%20enough%20to%20be%20in%20free%20public%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20I'm%20proposing%20a%20new%20acronym%20to%20go%20along%20with%20DINKs%2C%20DINKWADS%20(DINKS%20With%20A%20Dog)%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhenry-student-loans-six-figure-income-millennial-gen-z-retirement-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHENRYs%3C%2Fa%3E%20(High%20Income%2C%20Not%20Rich%20Yet).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20propose%20we%20call%20them%3A%20%3Cstrong%3EDIPS%2C%20or%20Double%20Income%2C%20Public%20School.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20of%20course%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-costs-raise-kid-us-americans-have-fewer-kids-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eolder%20kids%20and%20teens%20can%20be%20a%20financial%20drain%2C%20too%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20have%20costly%20activities%2C%20their%20clothes%20cost%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-one-year-returns-policy-explained-20230-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECat%20%26amp%3B%20Jack%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20need%20braces%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstanley-cups-tearing-apart-gen-alpha-middle-schools-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStanley%20cups%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20SAT%20prep%20classes.%20They%20eat%20a%20lot%20more%20(parents%20of%20teenage%20boys%20will%20confirm%2C%20sometimes%20%3Cem%3Ea%20lot%3C%2Fem%3E%20more)%20than%20babies.%20And%20don't%20forget%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-of-two-would-have-pay-8000-for-summer-camp-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esummer%20camp%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20are%20easily%20more%20than%20a%20mortgage%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20parents%20still%20hobbled%20by%20childcare%20costs%20are%20a%20different%20group%20from%20the%20DIPS.%20Let's%20call%20them%20%E2%80%A6%20%3Cstrong%3EPOLKs%2C%20or%20Parents%20of%20Little%20Kids.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENationwide%2C%20the%20average%20cost%20of%20childcare%20in%202022%20was%20around%20%2410%2C000%20a%20year%20per%20child%2C