20postpone%20other%20financial%20goals%20like%20home%20ownership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20gets%20better%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0I%20promise%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bad%20news%20for%20the%20POLKs%20is%20that%20life%20sucks%20right%20now.%20But%20you'll%20get%20through%20the%20diapers%2C%20the%20crayon%20on%20the%20walls%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fslate.com%2Fhuman-interest%2F2021%2F04%2Finvasion-of-the-berry-snackers.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrippling%20berry%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E.%20All%20parents%20look%20forward%20to%20watching%20their%20children%20grow%20and%20become%20little%20people%20with%20ideas%2C%20dreams%2C%20and%20interests%20of%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20most%20exciting%20part%20of%20all%20is%20that%20one%20day%2C%20they'll%20go%20off%20somewhere%20for%20six%20hours%20a%20day%20and%20learn%20a%20bunch%20of%20stuff%20%3Cem%3Efor%20free%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20noticed%20with%20some%20of%20my%20friends%20with%20older%20kids%20that%20there's%20a%20noticeable%20shift%20in%20their%20lives%20once%20their%20kids%20are%20in%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20friend%20bought%20a%20small%20vacation%20cabin%20upstate%2C%20and%20another%20started%20taking%20family%20vacations.%20I'm%20stuck%20in%20between%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0one%20kid%20in%20public%20school%20and%20a%20younger%20one%20still%20in%20day%20care.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20often%20dream%20of%20all%20the%20things%20we'll%20do%20with%20the%20extra%20cash%20we'll%20have%20once%20she's%20in%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20a%20contributor%20to%20Business%20Insider%20wrote%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmontessori-school-cost-mortgage-payment-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburdens%20of%20preschool%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20left%20her%20%248%2C000%20in%20credit%20card%20debt%20(even%20after%20getting%20grandparents'%20help%20to%20cover%20the%20tuition).%20%26quot%3BI%20cried%20the%20day%20my%20son%20was%20accepted%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplaces-with-free-pre-k-preschool-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epublic%20school%20pre-K%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENothing%20more%20beautiful%20than%20the%20moment%20a%20POLK%20becomes%20a%20DIPS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-paying-preschool-childcare-costs-new-term-dinks-dips-henry-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708854661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d9010c90413ab8e1d68cd2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-paying-preschool-childcare-costs-new-term-dinks-dips-henry-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lots%20of%20parents%20can't%20afford%20childcare%20and%20a%20mortgage.%20At%20least%20the%20POLKs.%20Just%20wait%20until%20they%20become%20DIPS%2C%20or%20Double%20Income%20Public%20School'ers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22knotopoulos%40businessinsider.com%20(Katie%20Notopoulos)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-paying-preschool-childcare-costs-new-term-dinks-dips-henry-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Consumption%20Expenditure%20Released%20After%2011-Year%20Gap%20Highlights%20Persisting%20Inequality%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25145200%2Fstreet-175277_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20poorest%205%25%20of%20India%20spend%20merely%20an%20average%20of%20Rs%2046%20daily%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20Rs%2067%20in%20urban%20areas%2C%20as%20against%20the%20richest%205%25%20whose%20daily%20consumption%20is%20Rs%20350%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20Rs%20700%20in%20urban%20parts%2C%20indicating%20a%20huge%20inequality%20in%20incomes%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Household%20Consumption%20Expenditure%20Survey%202022-23%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20released%20after%20a%20gap%20of%2011%20years%20revealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20bottom%205%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20rural%20population%2C%20ranked%20by%20MPCE%20(monthly%20per%20capita%20consumption%20expenditure)%2C%20has%20an%20average%20MPCE%20of%20%E2%82%B91%2C373%20while%20it%20is%20%E2%82%B92%2C001%20for%20the%20same%20category%20of%20population%20in%20the%20urban%20areas.%20The%20top%205%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20rural%20and%20urban%20population%2C%20ranked%20by%20MPCE%2C%20has%20an%20average%20MPCE%20of%20%E2%82%B910%2C501%20and%20%E2%82%B920%2C824%2C%20respectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20factsheet%20on%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20survey%2C%20released%20by%20the%20the%20Statistics%20and%20Programme%20Implementation%20Ministry%20on%20February%2024%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fthesundaystandard%2F2024%2FFeb%2F25%2Frs-46-per-person-consumption-a-day-by-poorest%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNEW%2520DELHI%2520%253A%2520The%2520poorest%25205%2CExpenditure%2520Survey%25202022%252D23%2520shows.%5C%22%3Ereleased%20the%20broad%20findings%20of%20the%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20carried%20out%20between%20August%202022%20and%20July%202023.%20The%20survey%20is%20usually%20conducted%20by%20the%20National%20Statistical%20Office%20every%20five%20years%20but%20the%20last%20report%20based%20on%20the%20survey%20in%202017-18%20after%20demonetisation%20and%20implementation%20of%20the%20the%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20(GST)%20was%20not%20released.%20The%20government%20cited%20%E2%80%9Cdata%20quality%E2%80%9D%20issues%20to%20stop%20its%20release.%20The%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20has%20been%20criticised%20for%20not%20collecting%20and%20sharing%20proper%20data%20on%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20report%20showed%20that%20although%20the%20average%20MPCE%20in%20urban%20households%20rose%20to%20Rs%203%2C510%20%E2%80%93%20an%20increase%20by%2033.5%25%20since%202011-12%20%E2%80%93%20and%20rural%20households%20to%20Rs%202008%20that%20is%20a%2040-42%25%20uptick%2C%20the%20jump%20is%20more%20owing%20to%20steep%20inflationary%20trends%20than%20any%20real%20rise%20in%20incomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20is%20proven%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20survey%20also%20revealed%20that%20the%20proportion%20of%20spending%20on%20food%20slid%20to%2046.4%25%20from%2052.9%25%20in%202011-12%20in%20rural%20households%2C%20while%20it%20dropped%20from%2042.6%25%20to%2039.2%25%20in%20the%20corresponding%20period%20for%20urban%20households.%20The%20figure%20could%20imply%20that%20people%20may%20be%20cutting%20down%20on%20spending%20on%20food%20because%20of%20high%20retail%20inflation%2C%20or%20have%20been%20relieved%20by%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20free%20ration%20scheme%20to%2080%20crore%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MPCE%20figures%20are%20based%20on%20data%20collected%20from%202%2C61%2C746%20households%2C%20of%20which%201%2C55%2C014%20were%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20spread%20over%20all%20States%20and%20Union%20Territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20MPCE%20numbers%20cited%20above%20do%20not%20take%20into%20account%20the%20imputed%20values%20of%20items%20received%20free%20of%20cost%20by%20individuals%20through%20various%20social%20welfare%20programmes%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fdistribution-of-5-kg-foodgrains-to-poor-under-pmgkay-extended-for-5-years-anurag-thakur%2Farticle67586389.ece%5C%22%3EPM%20Garib%20Kalyan%20Ann%20Yojana%20(PMGKAY)%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20State-run%20schemes%2C%20which%20were%20calculated%20separately%2C%20while%20including%20a%20few%20non-food%20items%20received%20through%20such%20schemes%2C%20including%20computers%2C%20mobile%20phones%2C%20bicycles%2C%20and%20clothing%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2FEconomy%2Fgovernment-puts-household-spending-report-on-hold%2Farticle61611660.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20average%20MPCE%2C%20at%202011-12%20prices%2C%20was%20a%20tad%20higher%20when%20these%20items%20were%20included%20while%20excluding%20free%20education%20and%20healthcare%20sops%20%E2%80%94%20at%20%E2%82%B92%2C054%20for%20rural%20households%2C%20and%20%E2%82%B93%2C544%20for%20urban%20homes%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESikkim%E2%80%99s%20MPCE%20is%20the%20highest%20among%20Indian%20states%20at%20Rs%207%2C731%20in%20rural%20and%20Rs%2012%2C%20105%20in%20urban%20households.%20Chhattisgarh%20was%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20ladder%20where%20the%20MPCE%20is%20Rs%202%2C466%20for%20rural%20and%20Rs%204%2C483%20for%20urban%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708853413000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25145200%2Fstreet-175277_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fconsumption-expenditure-released-after-11-year-gap-highlights-persisting-inequality%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20latest%20report%20showed%20that%20although%20the%20average%20MPCE%20in%20urban%20households%20rose%20to%20Rs%203%2C510%20%E2%80%93%20an%20increase%20by%2033.5%25%20since%202011-12%20%E2%80%93%20and%20rural%20households%20to%20Rs%202008%20that%20is%20a%2040-42%25%20uptick%2C%20the%20jump%20is%20more%20owing%20to%20steep%20inflationary%20trends%20than%20any%20real%20rise%20in%20incomes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ryan%20to%20perform%20%E2%80%98I%E2%80%99m%20Just%20Ken%E2%80%99%20at%20Oscars%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708853101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2F